[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi there,</p>\n<p>I wonder whether we should have <code>struct completion</code> abstractions in light of <code>CondVar</code>. Has this been discussed in the past? </p>\n<p>IIUC, we can apparently emulate a completion using a <code>CondVar</code> with no associated data, e.g.:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// fn wait_for_completion(some_condvar) {</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///     let lock: Mutex&lt;()&gt; = &lt;some useless mutex&gt;;</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///     some_condvar.wait(&amp;mut lock.lock());</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///  }</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// fn complete(some_condvar) {</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///    some_condvar.notify_all();</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// }</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But this is clunky, as we don't need the mutex, and frankly, that would be abusing the CondVar API, i.e.:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Condition</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">variables</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">are</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">typically</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">associated</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">boolean</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">predicate</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">condition</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">and</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mutex</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">The</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">predicate</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">always</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">verified</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inside</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mutex</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">before</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">determining</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">that</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">thread</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">must</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">block</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Thoughts?</p>",
        "id": 508841186,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1743193993
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you have a use case?</p>",
        "id": 508852206,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1743199274
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also notice that the semantics of <code>completion</code> is not the same as the <code>CondVar</code> code above. The above code may miss wake-ups if <code>complete()</code> happens before <code>wait_for_completion</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">complete</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"n\">wait_for_completion</span><span class=\"p\">();</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">// will wait here.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>whereas <code>completion</code> API avoids this.</p>",
        "id": 508965228,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1743288864
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The following is the rough idea of implementing <code>Completion</code> with <code>CondVar</code>, but obvious two problems: 1) <code>completion</code> reuses the wait queue's lock, but here we need another spinlock, 2) <code>completion</code> uses simple wait queue, but <code>CondVar</code> uses normal wait queues. See <code>include/linux/swait.h</code> for the differences.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Completion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">SpinLock</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">cond_var</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">CondVar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Completion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">wait_for_completion</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">lock</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">while</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">==</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cond_var</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wait</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">!=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">MAX</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">complete</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">lock</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">!=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">MAX</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"o\">++</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 508966314,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1743289810
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi Boqun,</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Do you have a use case?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes</p>\n<p>I think this solution is a bit of a reimplementation of struct completion itself. Shouldn't we just have an Opaque&lt;bindings::completion&gt; instead? or is that not possible?</p>",
        "id": 509177975,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1743422102
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, I don't think your code will work in IRQ context because it uses SpinLock instead of SpinLockIrq</p>",
        "id": 509179003,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1743422372
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"582628\">Daniel Almeida</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/struct.20completion.20abstractions.3F/near/509177975\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hi Boqun,</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Do you have a use case?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes</p>\n<p>I think this solution is a bit of a reimplementation of struct completion itself. Shouldn't we just have an Opaque&lt;bindings::completion&gt; instead? or is that not possible?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I meant to say if you have a use case, feel free to add a wrapper, because as I pointed out, your condvar implementation has a missing wake up problem.</p>",
        "id": 509197309,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1743426816
    }
]